---
import DefaultLayout from '@/layouts/DefaultLayout.astro';
import { Background } from '@/components/background';

const lastUpdated = "4 May 2026";
---

<DefaultLayout title="Terms of Service | Hooklyne" description="Hooklyne's terms of service. Subscription terms, billing, credits, cancellation, and the limits of liability for B2B prospect research.">
  <Background>
    <section class="pt-32 lg:pt-40 pb-20">
      <div class="container max-w-4xl">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[var(--hooklyne-blue)] mb-4">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] tracking-tight mb-4">Terms of Service.</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted-foreground)] mb-12">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

        <div class="space-y-10">

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] mb-3">1. Who these terms apply to</h2>
            <p class="text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed">
              These terms apply to any person or organisation that accesses or uses the Hooklyne service, including the portal, prospect research output, and any associated features. By creating an account or making a payment, you agree to these terms.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] mb-3">2. Subscriptions and billing</h2>
            <p class="text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed">
              Hooklyne is offered on a monthly or annual subscription basis. Subscriptions renew automatically at the end of each billing period unless cancelled before the renewal date. Annual plans are billed upfront for the full year. Prices are listed on our pricing page and may change with 30 days' notice to existing subscribers. Payments are processed by Stripe, Inc. Hooklyne does not store payment card details.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] mb-3">3. Credits</h2>
            <p class="text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed">
              Each subscription plan includes a monthly credit allowance. Credits are used when you request prospect packages, contact lookups, or other credit-consuming actions. Unused credits roll forward for one month up to a maximum of 2x your monthly allowance. Credits that exceed this cap expire. Credits have no cash value and are not refundable.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] mb-3">4. Cancellation and refunds</h2>
            <p class="text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed">
              You may cancel your subscription at any time. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period; you retain access and credits until then. Monthly subscriptions are not refunded for partial periods. Annual subscriptions may be eligible for a pro-rated refund within 14 days of purchase if no credits have been used. To request a refund, contact us at <a href="mailto:billing@hooklyne.com" class="text-[var(--hooklyne-blue)] hover:opacity-80">billing@hooklyne.com</a>.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] mb-3">5. Acceptable use</h2>
            <p class="text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed">
              You may use Hooklyne only for lawful B2B sales and marketing purposes. You may not resell, sublicense, or redistribute data or output generated by the service. You are responsible for ensuring your outreach complies with applicable law, including GDPR and the Dutch Telecommunications Act. Accounts found to be used for spam, scraping, or other abusive purposes will be suspended without refund.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] mb-3">6. Accuracy of information</h2>
            <p class="text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed">
              We take care to keep the information on this website accurate and up to date, but we make no guarantees about its completeness or accuracy. Pricing, features, and availability may change without notice. The most current information is always available by contacting us directly.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] mb-3">7. Prospect data accuracy</h2>
            <p class="text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed">
              Contact data provided through our service is sourced from third-party business data providers and publicly available sources. While we apply verification steps to improve accuracy, we cannot guarantee that all contact details are current or correct at the time of use. Individual results will vary depending on industry, target market, ICP quality, and how outreach is executed. We do not guarantee specific outcomes such as reply rates, meetings booked, or revenue generated.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] mb-3">8. No legal or compliance advice</h2>
            <p class="text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed">
              Nothing on this website constitutes legal advice. Customers are responsible for ensuring their use of Hooklyne, including the outreach they send, complies with applicable laws. We recommend consulting a legal adviser if you are unsure about your obligations.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] mb-3">9. Limitation of liability</h2>
            <p class="text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed">
              To the extent permitted by law, Hooklyne is not liable for any direct or indirect loss arising from use of this website or our service, including loss resulting from reliance on inaccurate prospect data, failed outreach, or service interruptions. Our total liability in any 12-month period is capped at the amount you paid for the service in that period.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] mb-3">10. Governing law</h2>
            <p class="text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed">
              These terms are governed by Dutch law. Any disputes are subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the competent courts in the Netherlands.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--heading)] mb-3">11. Contact</h2>
            <p class="text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed">
              For questions about these terms, contact us at <a href="mailto:legal@hooklyne.com" class="text-[var(--hooklyne-blue)] hover:opacity-80">legal@hooklyne.com</a>.
            </p>
          </section>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </Background>
</DefaultLayout>
